Nasarawa state House of Assembly on Monday received the nomination of 18 Overseers of the state’s  Development Areas from Governor Tanko Al-Makura for screening and confirmation. Speaker of the house Ibrahim Balarabe Abdullahi, disclosed this in Lafia after the majority leader, Tanko Tunga read the governor’s letter at the floor of the house.

The nominees include Amos Tsaku, Emma Yaro, Shuaibu Zanuwa, Suleiman Agyo, Bello Akoza, Obadia Agida, Ismaila Riri ,Hashimu Jada as Overseers of Agidi, Akun, Lafia-East, Lafia-North, Ekye, Jenkwe, Daddere and Azara development Areas respectively.

Others are Obadia Gomna, Joseph Dadu, Mikaila Salihu, Danladi Umar, Salihu Adamu, James Dantaro, Asibi Ubam, Usman Iliyasu, Halidu Sani and Ibrahim Saidu as Overseers of Akwanga West, Farin Ruwa, Agwada, Loko, Udege, Panda, Karshi, Umaisha,  Gadabuke and Giza Development Areas respectively.

Abdullahi said that their appointment would not only bring the government closer to the people at the grassroots but would also promote growth and development at the rural areas.

Abdullahi noted that the house slated August 29 for the screening of the nominees and directed the Clerk of the house to communicate to the appointees and they are to submit their Curriculum Vitae (CV), on Tuesday, August 28 for their screening.